READ(1)                     User Commands                     READ(1)

NAME
       read - read a line from stdin into variables

SYNOPSIS
       read [-r] [-p PROMPT] VAR [VAR2 ...]

DESCRIPTION
       Read a line from standard input and split it into variables.
       When multiple variables are given, the line is split on
       whitespace and assigned to each. The last variable receives
       all remaining words.

OPTIONS
       -p PROMPT  Display PROMPT before reading (no newline added)
       -r         Raw mode; do not interpret backslash escapes

EXIT STATUS
       0    Line was read successfully
       1    EOF or error

EXAMPLES
       echo "hello world" | read greeting
              Sets greeting="hello world"

       echo "a b c d" | read first second rest
              Sets first="a", second="b", rest="c d"

       cat users.txt | while read name email; do
           echo "User: $name, Email: $email"
       done
              Process file line by line (requires while loop support)

SEE ALSO
       echo(1), cat(1)
